+# GSG: Build, Install, and Validate the Three GPU Custom Operators
+
+This guide describes the three GPU custom operators in this source tree:
+
+- `SparseConvolution`: sparse convolution for both submanifold and regular/strided sparse layers. GPU implementation uses SYCL (Minuet v2 kernels with FP16 XMX GEMM, INT8 path, and SubM chain reuse). CPU implementation uses the core reference.
+- `SparseToDense`: scatter from sparse feature/coordinate form into a dense output tensor. GPU implementation uses SYCL. CPU implementation uses `parallel_for` over points.
+- `BevPoolV2`: view-transformation pooling operator for BEV feature generation. GPU implementation uses OpenCL v2 kernels. CPU implementation uses `parallel_for` over intervals.
+
+Each operator has both a GPU plugin implementation (SYCL or OCL) and a dedicated CPU plugin node.
+
+## 1. Build and Install
+
+Use the Intel oneAPI compiler toolchain. If CMake configures with the system `gcc`/`g++`, the SYCL custom primitive implementations are silently dropped from the GPU plugin.
+
+```bash
+cd <repo-root>
+source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh
+
+cmake -S . -B build \
+    -DCMAKE_DISABLE_FIND_PACKAGE_RapidJSON=ON \
+    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
+    -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=icx \
+    -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=icpx \
+    -DENABLE_TESTS=ON \
+    -DENABLE_PYTHON_API=ON \
+    -DENABLE_ONEDNN_FOR_GPU=ON \
+    -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$(pwd)/install
+
+cmake --build build --parallel $(nproc)
+
+cmake --install build --prefix $(pwd)/install
+```
+
+Confirm that CMake picked `icpx`:
+
+```bash
+grep CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER:FILEPATH build/CMakeCache.txt
+# Must show: .../oneapi/compiler/.../bin/icpx  (NOT /usr/bin/c++ or gcc)
+```
+
+After install, source the installed runtime before running external applications or benchmarks:
+
+```bash
+source install/setupvars.sh
+```
+
+### 1.1 Incremental builds (after code changes)
+
+For targeted rebuilds, specify targets explicitly:
+
+```bash
+# GPU plugin (SparseConvolution/SparseToDense SYCL, BevPoolV2 OCL)
+cmake --build build --parallel $(nproc) --target openvino_intel_gpu_plugin
+
+# CPU plugin (BevPoolV2, SparseToDense, SparseConvolution CPU nodes)
+cmake --build build --parallel $(nproc) --target openvino_intel_cpu_plugin
+
+# ONNX frontend (operator attribute parsing)
+cmake --build build --parallel $(nproc) --target openvino_onnx_frontend
+```
+
+> **Note**: After adding new source files to directories that use `GLOB_RECURSE`,
+> re-run the cmake configure step (without `rm -rf build`) so the new files
+> are picked up. Incremental `cmake --build` alone will not detect them.
+
+> **Note**: When the compiler is changed or `CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE` is not
+> set (empty in CMakeCache), `assert` statements in the GPU plugin are active
+> even in Release builds. Always pass
+> `-DCMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELEASE="-O3 -DNDEBUG" -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE="-O3 -DNDEBUG"`
+> to the configure step.
+
+## 2. Operator Test Matrix
+
+### 2.1 Core unit tests (shape inference + attribute serialization)
+
+These tests run on CPU without a GPU. They validate op registration, shape
+inference, and attribute round-trip serialization for all three operators.
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_core_unit_tests \
+    --gtest_filter='*BevPool*:*bevpool*:*SparseToDense*:*sparse_to_dense*:*SparseConvolution*:*sparse_convolution*' \
+    --gtest_color=no
+```
+
+Expected: 27 PASSED (10 BevPoolV2 + 9 SparseToDense + 8 SparseConvolution).
+
+### 2.2 GPU unit tests (GPU plugin kernel execution)
+
+These tests exercise the GPU implementations end-to-end with numerical accuracy
+checks against a CPU reference.
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests \
+    --gtest_filter='sparse_convolution_gpu_test.*:sparse_to_dense_gpu_test.*:BevPoolV2GpuTest.*' \
+    --gtest_color=no
+```
+
+Expected: 18 PASSED (12 SparseConvolution + 3 SparseToDense + 3 BevPoolV2).
+
+Narrower per-operator filters:
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests --gtest_filter='sparse_convolution_gpu_test.*'
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests --gtest_filter='sparse_to_dense_gpu_test.*'
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests --gtest_filter='BevPoolV2GpuTest.*'
+```
+
+### 2.3 CPU functional tests (CPU plugin node accuracy)
+
+These tests run inference on the CPU plugin and compare against the core reference
+(`ov::op::vX::*::evaluate()`). They exercise f32/f16 feature types, i32/i64 index
+types where applicable, and both static and dynamic input shapes.
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_cpu_func_tests \
+    --gtest_filter='*BevPool*:*SparseToDense*:*SparseConvolution*' \
+    --gtest_color=no
+```
+
+Expected: 42 PASSED (16 BevPoolV2 + 24 SparseToDense + 2 SparseConvolution).
+
+> **Note**: `SparseConvolution` core validates that the coords input is `i32`.
+> The CPU functional test therefore only covers `i32` index type.
+
+### 2.4 GPU functional tests (GPU plugin end-to-end accuracy)
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_func_tests \
+    --gtest_filter='*BevPool*:*SparseToDense*:*SparseConvolution*' \
+    --gtest_color=no
+```
+
+Expected: 26 PASSED (24 SparseToDense + 2 SparseConvolution). BevPoolV2 GPU
+functional tests have large-tensor shapes and may require significant GPU memory.
+
+### 2.5 Full sweep (all operators, all test binaries)
+
+```bash
+source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh
+
+FILTER='*BevPool*:*bevpool*:*SparseToDense*:*sparse_to_dense*:*SparseConvolution*:*sparse_convolution*'
+
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_core_unit_tests  --gtest_filter="$FILTER" --gtest_color=no
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests   --gtest_filter="$FILTER" --gtest_color=no
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_cpu_func_tests   --gtest_filter="$FILTER" --gtest_color=no
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_func_tests   --gtest_filter="$FILTER" --gtest_color=no
+```
+
+## 3. Quick Pass Criteria
+
+All three operators are considered validated when:
+
+| Test binary | Filter | Expected |
+|---|---|---|
+| `ov_core_unit_tests` | `*BevPool*:*SparseToDense*:*SparseConvolution*` | 27 PASSED |
+| `ov_gpu_unit_tests` | `*BevPool*:*sparse_to_dense*:*sparse_convolution*` | 18 PASSED |
+| `ov_cpu_func_tests` | `*BevPool*:*SparseToDense*:*SparseConvolution*` | 42 PASSED |
+| `ov_gpu_func_tests` | `*SparseToDense*:*SparseConvolution*` | 26 PASSED |
+
+## 4. External Integration Validation
+
+This source tree does not ship end-to-end model files or datasets. For
+integration validation, use an external model that contains these operators.
+
+Confirm the installed runtime is sourced first:
+
+```bash
+source install/setupvars.sh
+```
+
+Basic compile smoke test:
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/compile_tool -m <path-to-model> -d GPU
+```
+
+Basic inference smoke test:
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/benchmark_app -m <path-to-model> -d GPU
+```
+
+For sparse workloads, use real sparse coordinates rather than synthetic random
+inputs. Random int32 coordinates in a large spatial space produce near-empty
+kernel maps and give unrealistically low latency.
+
+## 5. Common Issues
+
+### Wrong compiler selected during CMake configure
+
+**Symptom**: Custom operators are missing at model load time, or the GPU plugin
+does not contain the SYCL implementations.
+
+**Fix**: Delete the build directory and reconfigure:
+
+```bash
+source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh
+rm -rf build
+
+cmake -S . -B build \
+    -DCMAKE_DISABLE_FIND_PACKAGE_RapidJSON=ON \
+    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
+    -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=icx \
+    -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=icpx \
+    -DENABLE_TESTS=ON \
+    -DENABLE_PYTHON_API=ON \
+    -DENABLE_ONEDNN_FOR_GPU=ON \
+    -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$(pwd)/install
+```
+
+### Assert fires in Release build (jitter macro or similar)
+
+**Symptom**: `Assertion failed` crash in `jitter.hpp` or similar during GPU
+inference or tests.
+
+**Cause**: `CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE` is empty in CMakeCache so `-DNDEBUG` is
+not passed; asserts remain active even in Release builds.
+
+**Fix**: Add the flags explicitly at configure time:
+
+```bash
+cmake -S . -B build \
+    ...  # existing flags
+    -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELEASE="-O3 -DNDEBUG" \
+    -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE="-O3 -DNDEBUG"
+```
+
+### New source files not picked up by incremental build
+
+**Cause**: Directories use `GLOB_RECURSE`; CMake does not re-scan unless
+reconfigured.
+
+**Fix**: Re-run `cmake -S . -B build` (keeping existing flags) after adding
+new files, then rebuild.
+
+### BevPoolV2 runs on CPU instead of GPU (slow inference)
+
+**Symptom**: Inference is 5–10× slower than expected on GPU.
+
+**Cause**: BevPoolV2 in the model is a dynamic-shape node. The OCL
+implementation is registered only for `static_shape`. With a CPU fallback also
+registered, the framework selects CPU for the dynamic node.
+
+**Fix**: `bevpool_v2_impls.cpp` must **not** list a CPU fallback for
+`dynamic_shape`. The current registry lists only the OCL static impl; the
+CPU node (`intel_cpu/src/nodes/bevpool_v2.cpp`) is the CPU plugin path, not
+the GPU plugin fallback. Verify `Registry<bevpool_v2>::get_implementations()`
+contains only `OV_GPU_CREATE_INSTANCE_OCL(ocl::BevPoolV2, shape_types::static_shape)`.
+
+### Sparse path performance is unexpectedly poor
+
+**Symptom**: SparseConvolution / SparseToDense GPU inference latency is much
+higher than expected.
+
+**Fix**: Rebuild with `icpx` (confirms SYCL implementations are compiled in),
+rerun the focused GPU unit tests, and confirm the GPU SYCL path is selected
+(not the CPU fallback) during integration testing.
